              <section>

                  
          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>Recently, it was announced that Alix Wilton-Regan will <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/new-tomb-raider-games-recast-lara-croft-with-a-gaming-veteran/1100-6536948/" data-ref-id="1100-6536948">take over for Camila Luddington</a> in the role of Lara Croft for the next two games in the series. In a new interview, she said she is afraid that it may all fall apart after the last game she was set to appear in, the Perfect Dark reboot, was canceled.</p><p>Wilton-Regan told <a href="https://www.thegamer.com/joanna-dark-perfect-dark-reboot-cancellation-details/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">TheGamer</a> that she was filming her scenes as Joanna Dark for the Perfect Dark game at the same time she was shooting Lara for the new Tomb Raider games. It was "wonderful and genuinely one of the most creatively exciting times of my life."</p>



    
