                <p>It's impossible to deny the success of Embark Studios' extraction shooter <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/arc-raiders/" data-ref-id="5000-546105">Arc Raiders</a>. Now, as 2025 comes to a close, the studio is reflecting on the momentous launch, which was recently capped off by the title's <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/all-the-game-awards-2025-winners-nominees/2900-7258/" data-ref-id="2900-7258">win for Best Multiplayer Game at the 2025 Game Awards</a>, and what's to come in 2026. If you're to believe Embark, which seems on top of the world right now, "the work is just beginning."</p><p>In a post to Arc Raiders <a href="https://arcraiders.com/news/1000-free-raider-tokens" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">website</a>, the shooter's executive producer Aleksander Grondal writes, "We had a feeling that Arc Raiders was something special. Internally, we were having a blast playing it before release, and your reaction to the tech test in April gave us an inkling of what was to come. What we didn't count on was the sheer scale of love and passion you guys were going to show this game."</p>



    
