          <p><em>Now Playing:</em> ARC Raiders - Flickering Flames Winter Event Overview Trailer</p>
      </div>
<p>Arc Raiders, which was released in late October, became a smash hit right out of the gate, selling millions of copies within days and solidifying itself as one of the most-beloved multiplayer games of the year. Though many multiplayer games enjoy a surge of popularity that eventually relents, Arc Raiders has held on impressively long. As of this writing, its <a href="https://steamdb.info/app/1808500/charts/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Steam numbers alone</a> are still in the six-digit realm.</p><p>Embark Studios seems intent to keep the ball rolling too. Arc Raiders has received consistent updates, addressing quality-of-life issues while simultaneously rolling out new features and even maps. The latest major update to the game, called <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/everything-new-in-the-arc-raiders-cold-snap-update/2900-7344/" data-ref-id="2900-7344">Cold Snap</a>, adds a new frosty map condition, in-game event, and more. It's just the first of <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/arc-raiders-roadmap-reveals-new-map-in-november-quests-and-more-in-the-months-ahead/1100-6535859/" data-ref-id="1100-6535859">many significant updates</a> which the team has already outlined.</p><p>"We're here for the long term, to build a game that continues to excite and surprise - we hope you stick around for the journey," reads the blog post. In addition, Embark is doling out a <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/arc-raiders-has-free-raider-tokens-for-you-right-now/1100-6537077/" data-ref-id="1100-6537077">free 1,000 Raider tokens</a>, an in-game currency, to anyone who plays the Winter event before it ends on January 13th.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
